[{"id":10,"guidance_id":10,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-04-28 15:42:57 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-13 19:09:27 UTC","text":"<p>If you have questions about creating a DMP or wish to find solutions for preserving and sharing your data, contact us at <a href=\"mailto:data.library@mcgill.ca\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">rdm.library@mcgill.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":11,"guidance_id":11,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 13:35:54 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-05 18:28:48 UTC","text":"<p>The University of Guelph Library provides support for researchers in determining the appropriate method and location for the preservation of data.</p>\r\n<p>We also maintain two research data respositories, the <a href=\"https://dataverse.scholarsportal.info/dataverse/ugardr\" target=\"_blank\">Agri-environmental Research Data Respository</a> and the <a href=\"https://dataverse.scholarsportal.info/dataverse/ugrdr\" target=\"_blank\">University of Guelph Research Data Repository</a>, where University of Guelph researchers can deposit their data through a facilitated process.</p>\r\n<p>Please see <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/preserving-sharing-data/preserving-your-data\" target=\"_blank\">Preserving Your Data</a> or contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a> for more information.</p>"},{"id":13,"guidance_id":13,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 13:41:50 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-05 13:54:37 UTC","text":"<p>Please see <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support/preservation\" target=\"_blank\">Preservation</a> and <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support/sharing-reuse\" target=\"_blank\">Sharing &amp; Reuse</a> for more information or contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a></p>"},{"id":14,"guidance_id":14,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 13:43:48 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-05 13:55:17 UTC","text":"<p>Please see <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support/sharing-reuse\" target=\"_blank\">Sharing &amp; Reuse - Conditions for Sharing</a> for more information on licensing options or contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a></p>"},{"id":15,"guidance_id":15,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 13:46:44 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-05 13:55:49 UTC","text":"<p>Please see <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support/organising-information\" target=\"_blank\">Organising Information</a> for more information regarding developing a strategy for how you will manage your project files throughout the research process including directory structure, file naming conventions and versioning.</p>\r\n<p>Please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a> for additional support.</p>"},{"id":16,"guidance_id":16,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 13:53:15 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-05 13:56:23 UTC","text":"<p>Review <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support/documenting-your-work\" target=\"_blank\">Documenting Your Work</a> for more information regarding creating and tracking metadata throughout the research process.</p>\r\n<p>Please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a> for additional support.</p>"},{"id":17,"guidance_id":17,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 13:54:59 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-05 13:56:53 UTC","text":"<p>Please see <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support/documenting-your-work\" target=\"_blank\">Documenting Your Work - Using Standards, Taxonomies, Classification Systems</a> for more about information about categorising and documenting your data or contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":18,"guidance_id":18,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 13:57:41 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-05 13:57:22 UTC","text":"<p>On campus, <a href=\"https://www.uoguelph.ca/ccs/\" target=\"_blank\">Computing and Communications Services (CCS)</a> provides support for short-term storage and backup.</p>\r\n<p>Please see <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support/storage-security\" target=\"_blank\">Storage &amp; Security</a> for more information or contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":19,"guidance_id":19,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 14:03:59 UTC","updated_at":"2018-06-12 18:11:11 UTC","text":"<p>On campus, <a href=\"https://www.uoguelph.ca/ccs/\" target=\"_blank\">Computing and Communications Services (CCS)</a> provides support for file security and encryption.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.uoguelph.ca/ccs/infosec\" target=\"_blank\">Information Security</a> services provided through the Office of the CIO, offers encryption and file security training.</p>\r\n<p>Please see <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support/storage-security\" target=\"_blank\">Storage &amp; Security</a> or contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a> for more information.</p>"},{"id":20,"guidance_id":20,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 14:12:07 UTC","updated_at":"2018-02-28 13:52:09 UTC","text":"<p>Researchers should consult the <a href=\"http://www.pre.ethics.gc.ca/eng/policy-politique/initiatives/tcps2-eptc2/Default/\" target=\"_blank\">Tri-Council Policy Statement: Ethical Conduct for Research Involvig Humans (TCPS2)</a> for information on ethical obligations.</p>\r\n<p>The University of Guelph's Office of Research offers guidance related to&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.uoguelph.ca/research/for-researchers/ethics-and-regulatory-compliance\" target=\"_blank\">Ethics and Regulatory Compliance</a> as well as <a href=\"http://www.uoguelph.ca/research/for-researchers/patenting-commercialization/ip-policy\" target=\"_blank\">Intellectual Property Policy</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Office of Research also provides resources, training and detailed guidance related to research involving human participants through the <a href=\"https://www.uoguelph.ca/research/services-divisions/ethics\" target=\"_blank\">Research Ethics/Protection of Human Participants</a> webpage.</p>\r\n<p>Please see <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support/sharing-reuse\" target=\"_blank\">Sharing &amp; Reuse</a> or contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a> for more information.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"},{"id":21,"guidance_id":21,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 14:19:54 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-05 13:58:51 UTC","text":"<p>The Tri-Council Policy Statement: Ethical Conduct for Research Involving Humans (Chapter 5) - <a href=\"http://www.pre.ethics.gc.ca/eng/policy-politique/initiatives/tcps2-eptc2/chapter5-chapitre5/#toc05-1d\" target=\"_blank\">D. Consent and Secondary Use of Identifiable Information for Research Purposes </a>provides detailed guidance related to secondary use of research data.</p>\r\n<p>Please see <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support/sharing-reuse\" target=\"_blank\">Sharing &amp; Reuse</a> or contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a> for more information on preparing your data for secondary use including obtaining consent, conditions for sharing and anonymising data.</p>"},{"id":22,"guidance_id":22,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 14:24:56 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-05 13:59:41 UTC","text":"<p>The University of Guelph Library provides training and support related to <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support\" target=\"_blank\">Research Data Management</a>. Please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a> for more information.</p>"},{"id":23,"guidance_id":23,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-24 14:39:15 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-05 14:00:25 UTC","text":"<p>The University of Guelph Library offers <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management\" target=\"_blank\">Research Data Management</a> services that support researchers with the organization, management, dissemination, and preservation of their research data.</p>\r\n<p>Data deposited in the University of Guelph Research Data Repositories is assigned a Digital Object Identifier (DOI) which provides a persistent URL (link) to your data. The DOI can be used to cite, improve discovery, track usage and measure the impact of your data.</p>\r\n<p>Sharing data through a repository can also improve its discovery and dissemination since repository content is fully indexed and searchable in search engines such as Google.</p>\r\n<p>For more information, contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":24,"guidance_id":24,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-28 13:55:30 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-05 14:01:54 UTC","text":"<p>The University of Guelph Library's <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data\" target=\"_blank\">Data Resource Centre</a> provides data collection and creation support including support for the design and creation of web surveys and access to data resources including numeric and geospatial databases.</p>\r\n<p>The Library also hosts the <a href=\"https://www.uoguelph.ca/brdc/\" target=\"_blank\">University of Guelph Branch Research Data Centre (BRDC)</a> where approved academic staff and students can securely access detailed microdata and administrative datasets from Statistics Canada.</p>\r\n<p>For more information, contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":25,"guidance_id":25,"locale":"en","created_at":"2016-11-28 14:11:28 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-05 14:02:52 UTC","text":"<p>The University of Guelph Library has created a <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/data-management-planning/checklist\" target=\"_blank\">Data Management Planning Checklist</a> which can be used to identify and keep track of the data management practices that you will utilize throughout the data life-cycle, including what information and tools will be used to document your work.</p>\r\n<p>For more information see <a href=\"https://www.lib.uoguelph.ca/get-assistance/maps-gis-data/research-data-management/training-support/documenting-your-work\" target=\"_blank\">Documenting Your Work</a> or contact us at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\" target=\"_blank\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":42,"guidance_id":42,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-05-31 21:52:39 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-21 21:50:40 UTC","text":"<p>If paying for an external hosting service, you will need to keep paying for it, or have some migration plan (e.g., depositing the data into a university repository). <a href=\"https://www.sfu.ca/itservices/collaboration/sfu-vault.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">SFU Vault</a> or services like <a href=\"https://www.sync.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sync</a> may be an option for some projects.</p>"},{"id":44,"guidance_id":44,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-05-31 21:57:11 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-21 21:51:06 UTC","text":"<p>Consider contacting <a href=\"mailto:data-services@sfu.ca\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">SFU Library Data Services</a> to develop the best solution for your research project.</p>"},{"id":45,"guidance_id":45,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-05-31 21:59:38 UTC","updated_at":"2017-07-21 22:32:28 UTC","text":"<p>If you need assistance locating a suitable data repository or archive, please contact&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:data-services@sfu.ca\" target=\"_blank\">SFU Library Data Services</a>. <a href=\"http://re3data.org\" target=\"_blank\">re3data.org</a>&nbsp;is a directory of potential open data repositories.</p>"},{"id":46,"guidance_id":46,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-05-31 22:03:04 UTC","updated_at":"2017-07-21 22:33:48 UTC","text":"<p>Some data formats are optimal for long-term preservation of data. For example, non-proprietary file formats, such as comma-separated ('.csv'), is considered preservation-friendly. SFU Library provides a useful table of <a href=\"http://www.lib.sfu.ca/help/publish/research-data-management/data-management-faqs\" target=\"_blank\">file formats for various types of data</a>. Keep in mind that preservation-friendly files converted from one format to another may lose information (e.g. converting from an uncompressed TIFF file to a compressed JPG file), so changes to file formats should be documented, and you may want to retain original formats, even if they are proprietary.</p>"},{"id":47,"guidance_id":47,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-05-31 22:05:15 UTC","updated_at":"2017-07-21 22:35:57 UTC","text":"<p>DDI is a common metadata standard for the social sciences. SFU Radar uses DDI Codebook to describe data so other researchers can find it by searching a discovery portal like <a href=\"https://search.datacite.org/\" target=\"_blank\">DataCite</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Read more about metadata standards: <a href=\"http://www.dcc.ac.uk/resources/metadata-standards\" target=\"_blank\">UK Digital Curation Centre's Disciplinary Metadata</a>.</p>"},{"id":48,"guidance_id":48,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-05-31 22:16:58 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-21 21:51:53 UTC","text":"<p>There are various creative commons licenses which can be applied to data. <a href=\"http://www.lib.sfu.ca/help/academic-integrity/copyright/authors/data-copyright\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Learn more about data &amp; copyright at SFU</a>.</p>"},{"id":49,"guidance_id":49,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-05-31 22:27:28 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-21 21:53:29 UTC","text":"<p>If possible, choose a repository like the Canadian Federated Research Data Repository, <a href=\"https://www.frdr-dfdr.ca/repo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">FRDR</a> for short,&nbsp; that will assign a persistent identifier (such as a DOI) to your dataset. This will ensure a stable access to the dataset and make it retrievable by various discovery tools. <a href=\"https://search.datacite.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">DataCite Search</a>&nbsp;is a discovery portal for research data. If you deposit in SFU Radar or a repository indexed in the <a href=\"http://www.re3data.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Registry of Research Data Repositories</a>, your records will appear in the portal's keyword search results.</p>"},{"id":50,"guidance_id":50,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-05-31 22:33:53 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-24 23:13:54 UTC","text":"<p>Decisions relevant to data retention and storage should align with SFU's Office of Research Ethics <a href=\"https://www.sfu.ca/ore/policies-and-guidelines.html\" target=\"_blank\">requirements</a>.</p>"},{"id":51,"guidance_id":51,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-05-31 22:34:12 UTC","updated_at":"2017-07-21 22:45:18 UTC","text":"<p>SFU's Office of Research Ethics' <a href=\"https://www.sfu.ca/ore/faqs/InformedConsent.html#main_content_title\" target=\"_blank\">consent statement</a> should be consulted when working with human participants.</p>\r\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.icpsr.umich.edu/icpsrweb/content/datamanagement/confidentiality/conf-language.html\" target=\"_blank\">Interuniversity Consortium for Political and Social Research</a> (ISPSR) and the <a href=\"http://www.ands.org.au/guides/sensitivedata\" target=\"_blank\">Australian National Data Service</a> also provide examples of informed consent language for data sharing.</p>"},{"id":52,"guidance_id":52,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-05-31 22:34:32 UTC","updated_at":"2017-07-21 22:46:20 UTC","text":"<p>The <a href=\"http://www.bclaws.ca/civix/document/id/complete/statreg/96165_01\" target=\"_blank\">BC Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act</a> doesn't apply to research information of faculty at post-secondary institutions (FIPPA S. 3(1)(e)). As such, there are no legal restrictions on the storage of personal information collected in research projects. This does not mean, however, that sensitive information collected as part of your research does not need to be safeguarded. Please refer to <a href=\"https://www.sfu.ca/policies/gazette/research/r20-01.html\" target=\"_blank\">University Ethics Review (R 20.01)</a>.</p>\r\n<p><em>IP issues should be clarified at the commencement of your research project so that all collaborators have a mutual understanding of ownership, to prevent potential conflict later.</em></p>"},{"id":54,"guidance_id":54,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-07-14 21:53:16 UTC","updated_at":"2017-07-21 22:48:06 UTC","text":"<p>If you need advice on identifying potential support, contact data-services@sfu.ca</p>"},{"id":55,"guidance_id":55,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-07-14 21:54:04 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-24 23:15:09 UTC","text":"<p>See more about best practices on file formats from the <a href=\"http://www.lib.sfu.ca/help/publish/research-data-management/data-management-faqs#which-file-formats-should-i-use-when-working-with-data\" target=\"_blank\">SFU Library.</a></p>"},{"id":56,"guidance_id":56,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-07-31 15:19:15 UTC","updated_at":"2017-07-31 15:19:15 UTC","text":"<p>test #1 <strong>texte gras</strong></p>"},{"id":57,"guidance_id":57,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-07-31 15:19:26 UTC","updated_at":"2017-07-31 15:19:26 UTC","text":"<p>test #1 <strong>texte gras</strong></p>"},{"id":58,"guidance_id":58,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-08-02 22:46:49 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-02 22:46:49 UTC","text":"<p><a href=\"http://libguides.uleth.ca/rdm\" target=\"_blank\">Research Data Management Guide</a></p>"},{"id":59,"guidance_id":59,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-08-02 22:47:00 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-02 22:47:00 UTC","text":"<p><a href=\"http://libguides.uleth.ca/rdm\" target=\"_blank\">Research Data Management Guide</a></p>"},{"id":60,"guidance_id":60,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-10-06 15:11:44 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-06 15:11:44 UTC","text":"<p>Les professionnels de l&rsquo;&eacute;quipe de soutien &agrave; la gestion des donn&eacute;es de recherche peuvent vous aider &agrave; trouver les informations n&eacute;cessaires pour compl&eacute;ter ce plan: <a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqam.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqam.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":61,"guidance_id":61,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-10-11 13:21:57 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-11 14:46:57 UTC","text":"<p>Les <a href=\"https://servicesinformatiques.uqam.ca/services/Exploitation%20pour%20la%20Recherche\" target=\"_blank\">Services informatiques</a> ont une offre de services en soutien &agrave; la recherche. Ils peuvent vous aider &agrave; d&eacute;terminer vos besoins de stockage et &agrave; mettre en place l&rsquo;infrastructure n&eacute;cessaire &agrave; votre projet de recherche.</p>"},{"id":62,"guidance_id":62,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-10-11 13:22:29 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-11 13:35:10 UTC","text":"<p>Les <a href=\"https://servicesinformatiques.uqam.ca/services/Exploitation%20pour%20la%20Recherche\" target=\"_blank\">Services informatiques</a> peuvent vous assister dans l'&eacute;laboration de votre strat&eacute;gie de sauvegarde.</p>"},{"id":63,"guidance_id":63,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-10-11 13:22:59 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-11 13:36:01 UTC","text":"<p>Les Services informatiques offrent une solution locale de stockage et de partage de fichiers, au sein de l'infrastructure de recherche de l&rsquo;UQAM: <a href=\"https://servicesinformatiques.uqam.ca/services/Service%20ownCloud\" target=\"_blank\">Service OwnCloud</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Les <a href=\"https://servicesinformatiques.uqam.ca/services/Exploitation%20pour%20la%20Recherche\" target=\"_blank\">Services informatiques</a> peuvent de plus vous aider &agrave; mettre au point les strat&eacute;gies de collaboration et de s&eacute;curit&eacute; entre vos diff&eacute;rents espaces de travail.</p>"},{"id":64,"guidance_id":64,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-10-11 13:23:44 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-11 14:49:43 UTC","text":"<p>Un professionnel de l&rsquo;&eacute;quipe de soutien &agrave; la gestion des donn&eacute;es de recherche peut vous aider &agrave; identifier des d&eacute;p&ocirc;ts pertinents pour vos donn&eacute;es: <a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqam.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqam.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":65,"guidance_id":65,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-10-11 13:24:16 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-11 14:49:28 UTC","text":"<p>La <a href=\"https://instances.uqam.ca/wp-content/uploads/sites/47/2017/09/Politique_no_10.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Politique de la recherche et de la cr&eacute;ation</a> (Politique no 10) de l&rsquo;UQAM souligne que &laquo; <em>le partage des r&eacute;sultats de la recherche et de la cr&eacute;ation avec la soci&eacute;t&eacute; est une n&eacute;cessit&eacute; dans le cadre d&rsquo;une politique de la recherche publique</em> &raquo; et que &laquo; <em>l&rsquo;UQAM encourage tous les acteurs de la recherche et de la cr&eacute;ation et en particulier les professeures et les professeurs &agrave; diffuser et transf&eacute;rer les r&eacute;sultats de leurs travaux au sein de la soci&eacute;t&eacute;</em> &raquo;.</p>\r\n<p>La <a href=\"http://www.science.gc.ca/eic/site/063.nsf/fra/h_83F7624E.html?OpenDocument\" target=\"_blank\">D&eacute;claration de principes des trois organismes sur la gestion des donn&eacute;es num&eacute;riques</a> n&rsquo;indique pas quelles donn&eacute;es doivent &ecirc;tre partag&eacute;es. Elle a pour objectif &laquo; <em>de promouvoir l&rsquo;excellence dans les pratiques de gestion et d&rsquo;intendance des donn&eacute;es num&eacute;riques de travaux de recherche financ&eacute;s par les organismes</em> &raquo;. Il y est d&eacute;crit de quelle fa&ccedil;on la&nbsp; pr&eacute;servation, la conservation et le partage des donn&eacute;es devraient &ecirc;tre envisag&eacute;s. &Agrave; lire!</p>\r\n<p>Suggestion: Voyez comment prot&eacute;ger vos donn&eacute;es sensibles (derni&egrave;re section du plan: &laquo;&nbsp;Conformit&eacute; aux lois et &agrave; l&rsquo;&eacute;thique&nbsp;&raquo;) et partagez tout ce qui peut l'&ecirc;tre, apr&egrave;s une analyse co&ucirc;t-b&eacute;n&eacute;fice.</p>"},{"id":66,"guidance_id":66,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-10-11 13:24:48 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-11 13:37:31 UTC","text":"<p>Les <a href=\"https://servicesinformatiques.uqam.ca/services/Exploitation%20pour%20la%20Recherche\" target=\"_blank\">Services informatiques</a> peuvent vous aider &agrave; d&eacute;terminer les co&ucirc;ts de l'infrastructure n&eacute;cessaire &agrave; votre projet de recherche.</p>"},{"id":67,"guidance_id":67,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-10-11 13:25:31 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-11 13:38:58 UTC","text":"<p>Les Services informatiques ont produit un &laquo; <a href=\"https://servicesinformatiques.uqam.ca/securite/30000740\" target=\"_blank\">Guide de bonnes pratiques pour la s&eacute;curit&eacute; informatique des donn&eacute;es de recherche</a> &raquo;.</p>"},{"id":68,"guidance_id":68,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-10-11 13:25:51 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-11 13:44:56 UTC","text":"<p>L&rsquo;&eacute;quipe de soutien &agrave; la gestion des donn&eacute;es de recherche peut vous mettre en relation avec des professionnels qualifi&eacute;s pour vous aider avec les questions d&rsquo;ordre &eacute;thique, juridique et de propri&eacute;t&eacute; intellectuelle: <a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqam.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqam.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":70,"guidance_id":70,"locale":"en","created_at":"2017-10-25 21:24:55 UTC","updated_at":"2017-10-25 21:24:55 UTC","text":"<div class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">Encrypting sensitive data is recommended. In almost cases,<span class=\"m_4424232124038497083m_5357280753526815954m_-8700388179308607917m_8993969591010721717m_-4744253511202436733m_-636808433971583107Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></span><em class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal;\">full disk encryption</em><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">&nbsp;is preferable;</span><em class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal;\">&nbsp;</em><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">users apply a</span><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">&nbsp;feature in the computer's operating system to encrypt&nbsp;the entire disk.</span>\r\n<div class=\"\" style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">In Windows, encryption of your internal disk or USB drives can be performed by a service called&nbsp;</span><em class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal;\">BitLocker</em><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">. In Mac OSX, disk encryption can be performed by a service called&nbsp;</span><em class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal;\">FileVault</em><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">. Documentation of these features is available from Microsoft or Apple. Full disk encryption is also available in Linux.&nbsp;Note that encrypting a USB drive may limit its&nbsp;usability across&nbsp;devices.</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">Encrypted data is less&nbsp;likely to be seen by an unauthorized person if the&nbsp;laptop/external drive is lost or stolen. I</span><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">t's important to consider that merely \"deleting\" files through Windows Explorer, Finder, etc. will not actually erase the data from the computer, and even &ldquo;secure deletion&rdquo; tools are not completely effective o</span><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">n&nbsp;modern disks</span><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">.&nbsp;Consider what security measures are&nbsp;necessary for handling sensitive data files and for decommissioning the&nbsp;computer disc&nbsp;at the end of its use.</span></span>\r\n<div class=\"\" style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span class=\"\" style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; float: none; display: inline ! important;\">For more information about securing sensitive research data, consult with <a href=\"https://www.sfu.ca/itservices.html\" target=\"_blank\">SFU's IT Services</a></span>.</div>"},{"id":72,"guidance_id":72,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-02-21 20:04:52 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-04 18:03:15 UTC","text":"<table width=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"792\">\r\n<p>For more information on file formats, see Concordia Library&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://library.concordia.ca/research/data/data-files.php?guid=file-formats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Research data management guide</a>.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>"},{"id":73,"guidance_id":73,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-02-21 20:06:20 UTC","updated_at":"2018-02-21 20:06:20 UTC","text":"<table width=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"792\">\r\n<p>For more information on metadata standards, see Concordia <a href=\"http://library.concordia.ca/help/data/metadata.php\" target=\"_blank\">Library&rsquo;s Research data management guide</a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>"},{"id":74,"guidance_id":74,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-02-21 20:07:23 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-04 18:04:58 UTC","text":"<p>For assistance with IT requirements definition and IT infrastructure &amp; solutions review or for help regarding business case preparation for new investment in IT infrastructure for researchers, please contact the Concordia <a href=\"https://www.concordia.ca/it/research.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">IT Research Support</a> Team.</p>"},{"id":75,"guidance_id":75,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-02-21 20:08:40 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-04 18:05:59 UTC","text":"<p>For more information on data storage and backup, see Concordia Library&rsquo;s <a href=\"http://library.concordia.ca/help/data/data-storage.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Research data management guide</a>.</p>\r\n<p>For assistance with data storage and backup, please contact Concordia's <a href=\"https://www.concordia.ca/it/research.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">IT Research Support</a> Team.</p>"},{"id":76,"guidance_id":76,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-02-21 20:09:58 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-04 18:07:30 UTC","text":"<table width=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"792\">\r\n<p>Datasets containing sensitive data or data files larger than 15MB should not be transferred via email.</p>\r\n<p>Please contact Concordia's <a href=\"https://www.concordia.ca/it/research.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">IT Research Support Team</a> for the exchange of files with external organizations or for assistance with other issues related to network services (connectivity with other external research centers or for high capacity, high volume data transfers). &nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>"},{"id":77,"guidance_id":77,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-02-21 20:11:28 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-04 18:08:24 UTC","text":"<p>For more information on data archiving options, see Concordia Library&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://library.concordia.ca/research/data/deposit-data.php?guid=where\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Research data management guide</a>.</p>"},{"id":78,"guidance_id":78,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-02-21 20:12:11 UTC","updated_at":"2018-02-21 20:12:11 UTC","text":"<table width=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"792\">\r\n<p>For more information, please contact&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:copyright.questions@concordia.ca\" target=\"_blank\">copyright.questions@concordia.ca</a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>"},{"id":79,"guidance_id":79,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-02-21 20:13:06 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-04 18:10:33 UTC","text":"<table width=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"792\">\r\n<p>Although there are no absolute rules to determine the cost of data curation, some guidelines and tools have been developed to help researchers estimate these costs. See for instance the <a href=\"https://www.ukdataservice.ac.uk/manage-data/plan/costing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">information and tool</a> provided by the UK Data Service.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.uu.nl/en/research/research-data-management/guides/costs-of-data-management\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Another version of this tool</a>, with examples of actual costs (in Euros), was developed by librarians and IT staff at Utrecht University.</p>\r\n<p>For assistance with IT requirements definition and IT infrastructure &amp; solutions review or for help regarding business case preparation for new investment in IT infrastructure for researchers, please contact Concordia's <a href=\"https://www.concordia.ca/it/research.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">IT Research Support</a> Team.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>"},{"id":80,"guidance_id":80,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-02-21 20:14:44 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-04 18:16:58 UTC","text":"<p>The answer to this question must be in line with Concordia University&rsquo;s <a href=\"http://www.concordia.ca/content/dam/common/docs/policies/official-policies/VPRGS-3-Sept.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Policy for the Ethical Review of Research Involving Human Participants</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The information provided here may be useful in completing section 13 (confidentiality, access, and storage) of the <a href=\"http://www.concordia.ca/research/for-researchers/ethics.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Summary Protocol Form (SPF)</a> for research involving human participants.</p>\r\n<p>For technical assistance, please contact Concordia's <a href=\"https://www.concordia.ca/it/research.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">IT Research Support</a> Team.</p>\r\n<p>For questions concerning ethics, Concordia's <a href=\"http://www.concordia.ca/research/for-researchers/assist-u.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Office of Research</a>.</p>"},{"id":81,"guidance_id":81,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-02-21 21:42:45 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-04 18:18:36 UTC","text":"<p>The information provided here may also be useful in completing section 13 (confidentiality, access, and storage) of the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.concordia.ca/research/for-researchers/ethics.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Summary Protocol Form (SPF)</a> for research involving human participants.</p>"},{"id":82,"guidance_id":82,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-02-21 21:44:34 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-04 18:26:23 UTC","text":"<table width=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"792\">\r\n<p>Concordia University researchers must abide by the University&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://www.concordia.ca/about/policies/theme.html#research\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">policies related to research</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Intellectual property issues at Concordia University are governed by the <a href=\"http://www.concordia.ca/content/dam/common/docs/policies/official-policies/VPRGS-9.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Policy on Intellectual Property (VPRGS-9) </a>as well as <a href=\"http://cufa.net/collective-agreements/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">CUFA</a> and <a href=\"https://cupfa.org/collective-agreement/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">CUPFA</a> collective agreements.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For more information on intellectual property or copyright issues, please contact&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:copyright.questions@concordia.ca\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">copyright.questions@concordia.ca</a></p>\r\n<p>For more information on research ethics please contact Concordia's <a href=\"http://www.concordia.ca/research/for-researchers/assist-u.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Office of Research</a>.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>"},{"id":83,"guidance_id":83,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-06-12 18:04:35 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-20 15:37:20 UTC","text":"<p>Give a brief description of the project data including data to be generated, collected, or acquired from third-party sources.</p>\r\n<p>List the data types (e.g. numeric) that will be collected and the formats (e.g. Excel) that will be used during the project.</p>\r\n<p>Estimate the size (storage space in MB/GB/TB) of the data that will be included in this study.</p>\r\n<p>Provide a sense of the scope of the study (e.g. number of subjects or sites)</p>\r\n<p>Indicate where the data will be stored. It is recommended that more than one storage solution be used. Detail security measures that will protect that data throughout the project.</p>\r\n<p>Provide details of how project files will be organized to ensure usability and findability. Give some consideration to how folders and files will be named for consistency and lack of ambiguity.</p>\r\n<p>Indicate what metadata and/or documentation will be developed to accompany your data files.</p>\r\n<p>Checklist of points to cover in your response:</p>\r\n<p>&bull; overview of data *<br />&bull; source of data<br />&bull; data types<br />&bull; file formats *<br />&bull; size<br />&bull; scope<br />&bull; storage location *<br />&bull; backup<br />&bull; data organization<br />&bull; naming conventions<br />&bull; metadata, documentation</p>\r\n<p>* Items with an asterisk are essential for an acceptable DMP</p>"},{"id":85,"guidance_id":85,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-06-12 18:13:34 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-20 16:02:02 UTC","text":"<p>Outline plans for the preservation of your data post-project. Include details such as how long the data will be preserved and the location of where the data will be held (for example, name and URL of repository selected).</p>\r\n<p>If only part of the dataset will be preserved/shared, indicate where the remainder of the data will be kept, for what length of time, and who will have access. If destroying data, indicate how you will record and store this information.</p>\r\n<p>For researchers opting to preserve their data in the local U of G data repositories, the following language could be copied into the preservation section of the plan:</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;<em>(Raw, processed, analyzed or final) _____ data from this project will be deposited into the Agri-environmental Research Data Repository (<a href=\"https://dataverse.scholarsportal.info/dataverse/ugardr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://dataverse.scholarsportal.info/dataverse/ugardr</a>) along with relevant supplemental files through a facilitated deposit process managed by the University of Guelph Library. This (Dataverse) system, hosted in Canada on University of Toronto servers, is maintained and backed up by Scholars Portal according to high quality systems standards as part of a larger network of Canadian repositories. Each project is assigned a unique DOI (digital object identifier) which can be used in reporting, sharing, publishing and journal submissions to provide a permanent link to the location of the data. The PI will determine the level of access available to users and the conditions under which the data can be used by third parties.</em>&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>NOTE: Food from Thought researchers must submit any data related to publications to this repository.</p>\r\n<p>Checklist of points to cover in your response:</p>\r\n<p>&bull; repository identified *<br />&bull; which data will be preserved<br />&bull; plan for non-preserved data; destruction?</p>\r\n<p>* Items with an asterisk are essential for an acceptable DMP</p>"},{"id":86,"guidance_id":86,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-06-12 18:13:59 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-20 18:49:53 UTC","text":"<p>If your data has been collected and managed in a proprietary format it should be converted to plain text for preservation.</p>\r\n<p>Include documentation, coding and scripts or other material required to replicate results.</p>\r\n<p>Include metadata to ensure your data can be interpreted and analyzed appropriately.</p>\r\n<p>Checklist of points to cover in your response:</p>\r\n<p>&bull; data transformation *<br />&bull; supporting documentation<br />&bull; metadata</p>\r\n<p>* Items with an asterisk are essential for an acceptable DMP</p>"},{"id":88,"guidance_id":88,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-06-12 18:16:58 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-20 19:14:28 UTC","text":"<p>Explain whether you will be sharing your data through the UG data repository or an external data repository. Mention whether an embargo will need to be applied before your data is available for sharing.</p>\r\n<p>If your data will be shared in a more limited way (i.e. not openly available to everyone) explain who will have access and why this limitation is necessary.</p>\r\n<p>If you are not able to share your data, please explain the constraints that prevent sharing.</p>\r\n<p>Consideration should be given to selecting an appropriate end-user license for the data. Note that only the intellectual property rights holder(s) can issue a license.</p>\r\n<p>Checklist of points to cover in your response:</p>\r\n<p>&bull; decision to share *<br />&bull; repository identified *<br />&bull; with whom (openly or selectively shared) *<br />&bull; licensing of data</p>\r\n<p>* Items with an asterisk are essential for an acceptable DMP</p>"},{"id":89,"guidance_id":89,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-09-12 13:41:44 UTC","updated_at":"2018-09-12 13:41:44 UTC","text":"<p>Les professionnels de l&rsquo;&eacute;quipe de soutien &agrave; la gestion des donn&eacute;es de recherche peuvent vous aider &agrave; trouver les informations n&eacute;cessaires pour compl&eacute;ter ce plan: <a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqam.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqam.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":90,"guidance_id":90,"locale":"en","created_at":"2018-10-05 18:50:20 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-20 19:07:54 UTC","text":"<p>Outline any restrictions to data handling, sharing and/or preservation as a result of ethical, legal, or commercial requirements or limitations. Show that you are aware of the issues and have planned accordingly.</p>\r\n<p>Details should include reference to specific requirements outlining the entity involved and the nature of the limitation (for example, restrictions on reuse of third-party data). If an embargo is required due to publication or research needs, provide details including length of time data will be restricted.</p>\r\n<p>Checklist of points to cover in your response:</p>\r\n<p>&bull; details of restrictions or constraints *<br />&bull; need for embargo</p>\r\n<p>* Items with an asterisk are essential for an acceptable DMP</p>"},{"id":91,"guidance_id":91,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 13:39:29 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-02 21:16:09 UTC","text":"<p>Pour de l'information g&eacute;n&eacute;rale et des conseils sur la gestion des donn&eacute;es de recherche (GDR), consultez le <a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/pls/public/gscw030?owa_no_site=5513\" target=\"_blank\">guide &eacute;labor&eacute; par le Service de la biblioth&egrave;que</a> de l'Universit&eacute; du Qu&eacute;bec &agrave; Trois-Rivi&egrave;res. Pour toute question, vous pouvez contacter un professionnel &agrave; <a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqtr.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqtr.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":93,"guidance_id":93,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 13:47:54 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-12 17:28:31 UTC","text":"<p>L'utilisation de formats propri&eacute;taires (ex. .XLS) peut &ecirc;tre justifi&eacute;e durant le projet.</p>\r\n<p>Cela dit, la conversion en un format ouvert (ex. .CSV) en fin de projet peut entra&icirc;ner des pertes d'information. Il est donc conseill&eacute; dans la mesure du possible d'utiliser d&egrave;s le d&eacute;but du projet des formats ouverts.</p>"},{"id":94,"guidance_id":94,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 13:49:43 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-19 19:30:15 UTC","text":"<p>Plus d'informations sur les bonnes pratiques en mati&egrave;re de nommage de fichiers et de gestion des versions sont disponibles dans le <a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/pls/public/gscw031?owa_no_site=5513&amp;owa_no_fiche=9&amp;owa_bottin=#nommage\" target=\"_blank\">guide sur la GDR</a>.</p>"},{"id":95,"guidance_id":95,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 14:58:13 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-19 19:37:27 UTC","text":"<p>Cette question vise &agrave; s'assurer que vos donn&eacute;es pourront &ecirc;tre comprises par un utilisateur &eacute;tranger au projet. L'utilisation d'un dictionnaire de donn&eacute;es pourrait r&eacute;pondre &agrave; ce besoin.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pour plus d'informations, consultez le <a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/pls/public/gscw031?owa_no_site=5513&amp;owa_no_fiche=8&amp;owa_bottin=#documentation\" target=\"_blank\">guide sur la GDR</a>.</p>"},{"id":96,"guidance_id":96,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 15:55:53 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-19 19:38:05 UTC","text":"<p>Cette question vise &agrave; s'assurer que la documentation relative aux donn&eacute;es de recherche du projet est pr&eacute;vue dans votre processus de travail. L'utilisation d'un dictionnaire de donn&eacute;es, d'un cahier de laboratoire et d'un fichier lisez-moi sont autant de&nbsp;fa&ccedil;on de r&eacute;pondre aux exigences des organismes subventionnaires.</p>\r\n<p>Pour plus d'informations, consultez le&nbsp;<a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/pls/public/gscw031?owa_no_site=5513&amp;owa_no_fiche=8&amp;owa_bottin=#documentation\" target=\"_blank\">guide sur la GDR</a>.</p>"},{"id":97,"guidance_id":97,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 17:40:31 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-19 19:39:29 UTC","text":"<p>Selon le d&eacute;p&ocirc;t de donn&eacute;es choisi, les m&eacute;tadonn&eacute;es &agrave; consigner peuvent varier. Pour toute question concernant les m&eacute;tadonn&eacute;es &agrave; entrer dans le d&eacute;p&ocirc;t Dataverse de l'UQTR, &eacute;crivez-nous &agrave; <a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqtr.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqtr.ca</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Des informations g&eacute;n&eacute;rales sur les m&eacute;tadonn&eacute;es sont disponibles dans le <a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/pls/public/gscw031?owa_no_site=5513&amp;owa_no_fiche=8&amp;owa_bottin=\" target=\"_blank\">guide sur la GDR</a>.</p>"},{"id":98,"guidance_id":98,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 17:42:26 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-19 17:43:48 UTC","text":"<p>Pour toute question &agrave; ce sujet, &eacute;crivez-nous &agrave; <a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqtr.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqtr.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":99,"guidance_id":99,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 17:46:30 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-19 19:33:03 UTC","text":"<p>Des informations sur les bonnes pratiques de stockage sont disponibles dans le <a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/pls/public/gscw031?owa_no_site=5513&amp;owa_no_fiche=9&amp;owa_bottin=\" target=\"_blank\">guide sur la GDR</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Disponible pour tous les employ&eacute;s, l'Espace UQTR permet le stockage de jusqu'&agrave; 10Go de donn&eacute;es dans un espace s&eacute;curitage et accessible &agrave; distance.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pour toute demande relative au stockage des donn&eacute;es &agrave; l'UQTR, &eacute;crivez-nous &agrave; <a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqtr.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqtr.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":100,"guidance_id":100,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 19:26:28 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-02 16:23:10 UTC","text":"<p>Il faut d&eacute;montrer ici que le partage des donn&eacute;es entre les membres de l'&eacute;quipe de recherche ne compromet pas le caract&egrave;re confidentiel de certaines donn&eacute;es sensibles, le cas &eacute;chant. Pour toute question &agrave; ce sujet, &eacute;crivez &agrave; <a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqtr.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqtr.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":101,"guidance_id":101,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 19:37:49 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-19 19:38:11 UTC","text":"<p>En plus du d&eacute;p&ocirc;t Dataverse de l'UQTR, des centaines d'autres d&eacute;p&ocirc;ts de donn&eacute;es sont disponibles et peuvent accueillir vos donn&eacute;es. Pour plus d'informations &agrave; ce sujet, consultez le <a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/pls/protege/gscw031?owa_no_site=5513&amp;owa_no_fiche=6\" target=\"_blank\">guide sur la GDR</a>.&nbsp;</p>"},{"id":102,"guidance_id":102,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 19:46:02 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-19 19:46:02 UTC","text":"<p>Contactez-nous pour plus d'informations &agrave; ce sujet : <a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqtr.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqtr.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":103,"guidance_id":103,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 19:52:55 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-19 19:33:57 UTC","text":"<p>La <a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/vrsg/Reglementation/152.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">politique sur le libre acc&egrave;s aux r&eacute;sultats de recherche</a> de l'UQTR : &laquo; encourage en particulier la diffusion des connaissances aupr&egrave;s de la communaut&eacute; scientifique et des utilisateurs des r&eacute;sultats de la recherche. &raquo; (p. 2)</p>\r\n<p>Toutes les donn&eacute;es n'ont pas &agrave; &ecirc;tre partag&eacute;es. Cela dit, selon la <a href=\"http://www.science.gc.ca/eic/site/063.nsf/fra/h_83F7624E.html?OpenDocument\" target=\"_blank\">D&eacute;claration de principes des trois organismes sur la gestion des donn&eacute;es num&eacute;riques</a><br /> : &laquo;Pour d&eacute;terminer si des donn&eacute;es doivent &ecirc;tre pr&eacute;serv&eacute;es et partag&eacute;es, les chercheurs devraient examiner quelles donn&eacute;es sont n&eacute;cessaires pour valider les conclusions et les r&eacute;sultats de la recherche et pour r&eacute;pliquer et r&eacute;utiliser les r&eacute;sultats&raquo;.&nbsp;</p>"},{"id":104,"guidance_id":104,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-10-19 19:54:30 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-19 19:34:27 UTC","text":"<p>La tendance g&eacute;n&eacute;rale est aux licences les plus ouvertes possible. Pour plus d'informations &agrave; ce sujet, consultez le <a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/pls/protege/gscw031?owa_no_site=5513&amp;owa_no_fiche=10\" target=\"_blank\">guide sur la GDR</a>.&nbsp;</p>"},{"id":105,"guidance_id":105,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-11-01 23:03:29 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-01 23:03:29 UTC","text":"<p>Vous pouvez contacter un professionnel &agrave;&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqtr.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqtr.ca</a>&nbsp;pour obtenir de l'aide concernant l'estimation de ces co&ucirc;ts.&nbsp;</p>"},{"id":106,"guidance_id":106,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-11-01 23:05:30 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-01 23:05:30 UTC","text":"<p>Les Services informatiques de l'UQAM ont produit un &laquo;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://servicesinformatiques.uqam.ca/securite/30000740\" target=\"_blank\">Guide de bonnes pratiques pour la s&eacute;curit&eacute; informatique des donn&eacute;es de recherche</a>&nbsp;&raquo;. Pour toute question &agrave; ce sujet, contactez un professionnel &agrave; gdr@uqtr.ca.</p>"},{"id":107,"guidance_id":107,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-11-01 23:06:50 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-19 19:35:12 UTC","text":"<p>Le <a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/pls/public/gscw031?owa_no_site=5513&amp;owa_no_fiche=11&amp;owa_bottin=\" target=\"_blank\">guide sur la GDR</a> comprend plus de pr&eacute;cisions sur la question des donn&eacute;es sensibles.</p>\r\n<p>Contactez-nous pour&nbsp;toute question &agrave; ce sujet :&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqtr.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqtr.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":108,"guidance_id":108,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2018-11-01 23:12:46 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-01 23:12:46 UTC","text":"<p>Contactez-nous pour&nbsp;toute question &agrave; ce sujet :&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqtr.ca\" target=\"_blank\">gdr@uqtr.ca</a>.</p>"},{"id":110,"guidance_id":110,"locale":"en","created_at":"2019-01-28 13:28:55 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-20 19:42:20 UTC","text":"<p>Explain whether you will be sharing all of your data or only a subset. Explain the reasons. Which version of the data will you share?</p>\r\n<p>Checklist of points to cover in your response:</p>\r\n<p>&bull; all data to be shared or subset identified *<br />&bull; version of data</p>\r\n<p>* Items with an asterisk are essential for an acceptable DMP</p>"},{"id":111,"guidance_id":111,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2019-10-29 17:54:02 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-29 18:02:14 UTC","text":"<p>En tout temps, vous pouvez communiquer avec <a href=\"mailto:gdr@inrs.ca\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">gdr@inrs.ca</a> pour obtenir de l'aide concernant votre plan de gestion de donn&eacute;es ou pour la gestion de vos donn&eacute;es de recherches.</p>\r\n<p>Consultez la fiche conseil &laquo; Les formats de vos donn&eacute;es : pensez-vous &agrave; long terme? &raquo; pour r&eacute;pondre &agrave; cette question.</p>"},{"id":112,"guidance_id":112,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2019-10-29 17:54:45 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-29 17:54:45 UTC","text":"<p>Consultez la fiche conseil &laquo; Les formats de vos donn&eacute;es : pensez-vous &agrave; long terme? &raquo; pour r&eacute;pondre &agrave; cette question.</p>"},{"id":113,"guidance_id":113,"locale":"fr","created_at":"2019-10-29 17:55:49 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-29 17:55:49 UTC","text":"<p>Consultez la fiche conseil &laquo; Conseils pour nommer et structurer vos fichiers &raquo; pour r&eacute;pondre &agrave; cette question.</p>"}]